  "sections": {
    "Background": {
      "text": "Benign and self-limited condition of the epiploic appendages (fat-filled sacs along surface of colon and rectum)\n[1]\nAcutely inflamed due to torsion or venous thrombosis\nMimics\nAppendicitis\nor\nDiverticulitis\nMost often found on abdominal CT during abdominal pain workup\nMore than half occur in rectosigmoid colon",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
    "Clinical_Features": {
      "text": "Abdominal pain\nMay develop\nfever\nand\nleukocytosis",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
